  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age equal or above 18 years old

          -  Temporary double enterostomy treated by chyme reinfusion as a routine primary care

          -  Downstream bowel of at least 25 cm of healthy small bowel, accessible by a stoma, and
             suitable for chyme reinfusion and ileal biopsy

          -  In case of enterocutaneous fistula, diagnosis of fistula origin and localization
             confirmed by additional medical imaging (computerized tomography/fistulography)

          -  Written informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with a mental disability

          -  Pregnancy or lactation

          -  Hepatocellular carcinoma

          -  Blood coagulation disorders

          -  Shock of any cause

          -  Patients subject to major legal protection (safeguarding justice, guardianship,
             trusteeship), persons deprived of liberty
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
